<hr>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of 
your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Author&#8217;s name. &#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Name of Publication</em> 
		volume.issue (year of publication): page numbers. Medium of publication.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		&#45;&nbsp;&#45;&nbsp;&#45;. &#34;Title of article.&#34; <em>Name of Publication</em> 
		volume.issue (year of publication): page numbers. Medium of publication.
	</div>
</blockquote>
<br>
Give the author&#8217;s name in the first entry only. After that use three hyphens, followed by a 
fullstop. References with the same first author and a different second or third author are listed 
alphabetically.
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Smith, Andrew</span>. 
		&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Leading by Example</span>.&#34; 
		<em><span class="hover" title="Name of Publication">Management Research International</span></em> 
		<span class="hover" title="volume">3</span>.<span class="hover" title="issue">4</span> 
		(<span class="hover" title="year of publication">2056</span>): 
		<span class="hover" title="page numbers">45&#45;48</span>. 
		<span class="hover" title="Medium of publication">Print</span>.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		&#45;&nbsp;&#45;&nbsp;&#45;. &#34;Teaming with Wildlife: Promoting Team Development 
		through Volunteer Service at Auckland Zoo.&#34; 
		<em>New Zealand Business Review</em> 17.4 (2050): 230&#45;40. 
		<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Print</span>.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Smith, Andrew and Bev Brown. &#34;Learning Through Teaching&#34; 
		<em>Teaching and Learning in Higher Education</em> 3.4 (2056): 45&#45;48. 
		<span class="hover" title="Author&#8217;s name">Print</span>.
	</div>
</blockquote>
